Every five minutes, every person Mabotse Matloha comes into close contact with in her normal shift could be potentially infected with the significantly contagious Covid-19, but the mother of three from Limpopo could not be any prouder. Her protective goggles, mask, gown and gloves are her barriers between herself and the danger potentially lurking in the queue of people lining up to have her take their samples to be tested for Covid-19 at Lancet Laboratories in Sandton. “I was worried but now I am wearing PPE (personal protective equipment). I think I am 100% sure nothing will come against me,”...